3. TEST COMPOSITION
	3.1 2D ML10 - VO data
		FOR ALL MODELS:	
			PHRASE_SPACE: ANY OUTPUT FROM 2.1
			(preferably matching settings with ARG_SPACE)
			TRAIN_DATA:
				/mnt/cimec-storage-sata/users/georgiana.dinu/COLING/per_in/:
					ML10_VO_train.txt (281783 total samples, 63 verbs)
			
			INPUT DATA FOR COMPOSE:
				/mnt/cimec-storage-sata/users/georgiana.dinu/COLING/test/ML10/:
					ML10_VO_test.txt (72 elements)
				!!!This will output a composed space
			
			SIMILARITY TEST DATA WITH THE COMPOSED SPACE:
				/mnt/cimec-storage-sata/users/georgiana.dinu/COLING/test/ML10/:
					ML10data_new.txt 
					words: columns 1,2
					gold: column 3
					test: pearson,spearman				
			
		3.1.1 LexicalFunction
			BOTH TRAIN AND COMPOSE:
				ARG_SPACE: ANY OUTPUT FROM 1.1
							
		3.1.2 WeightedAdditive							
			BOTH TRAIN AND COMPOSE:
				ARG_SPACE1 = ARG_SPACE2: ANY OUTPUT FROM 1.1
				
		3.1.3 FullAdditive
			BOTH TRAIN AND COMPOSE:
				ARG_SPACE1 = ARG_SPACE2: ANY OUTPUT FROM 1.1
						
		3.1.4 Dilation
			BOTH TRAIN AND COMPOSE:
				ARG_SPACE1 = ARG_SPACE2: ANY OUTPUT FROM 1.1


	3.2 3D GS11 - SVO data
		3.1.1 LexicalFunction
			3.1.1.1. TRAIN PHASE 1 (run this with --export_params)
					ARG_SPACE:
						ANY OUTPUT FROM 1.1
					PHRASE_SPACE:
						SPACE FROM 2.2 (peripheral SVO space)
					
					TRAIN DATA:
						/mnt/cimec-storage-sata/users/georgiana.dinu/COLING/per_in/:
							GS11_SVO_train.txt (459946 total samples, ?# vo functions)
	
					OUTPUT THE LEARNED VO SPACE by using --export_params
					
			3.1.1.2. TRAIN PHASE 2
					ARG_SPACE:
						ANY OUTPUT FROM 1.1
					PHRASE_SPACE:
						SPACE RESULTED IN 3.1.1.1 (1. load the compositional mode, 
													and get the space out of it,
													or 
												   2.run the previous step with 
													--export_params, and use that
													space)
					
					TRAIN DATA:
						/mnt/cimec-storage-sata/users/georgiana.dinu/COLING/per_in/:
							GS11_V_train.txt (122330 total samples, 30 verbs
											  a lot of the samples will be ignored
											  because they contain VO s which have not been trained
											  due to lack of sufficient train data)										
					
					OUTPUT THE LEARNED V SPACE by using --export_params
					
					
			3.1.1.3 COMPOSE SVO (i.e. build an SVO space)
					1. LOAD THE LEARNED V SPACE (FROM 3.1.1.2)
					2. COMPOSE STEP 1 ON DATA:
						ARG_SPACE: any suitable noun space
						FUNCTION SPACE: the V one learned in 3.1.1.2
						DATA:
							/mnt/cimec-storage-sata/users/georgiana.dinu/COLING/test/GS11/:
								GS11compose1.txt (299 lines)
						OUTPUT THE RESULTED COMPOSED SPACE (VO SPACE)
					
					3. COMPOSE STEP 2 ON DATA:	
					4. LOAD THE PREVIOUS VO SPACE FROM STEP 2	
					5. CREATE A LEXICAL FUNCTION COMPOSITON WITH IT
						(using "function_space=")
						ARG_SPACE: any suitable N space
						FUNCTION SPACE: the VO space
						DATA:
						/mnt/cimec-storage-sata/users/georgiana.dinu/COLING/test/GS11/:
								GS11compose2.txt (299 lines)
						OUTPUT THE RESULTED COMPOSED SPACE (SVO SPACE)	
	
	
			3.1.1.4 TEST SIMILARITIES WITH THE COMPOSED SPACE
					LOAD THE LAST COMPOSED SPACE FROM 3.1.1.3 (contains svo s)
							
					COMPUTE SIMILARITIES ON DATA:
						/mnt/cimec-storage-sata/users/georgiana.dinu/COLING/test/GS11/:
							GS11data_new.txt (2500 lines)
							words: columns 1,2
							gold: column 3
			 
	
	
	
